message.content:
1. Students watched the CAL package.
2. Students read the information leaflet.
3. The retention performance percentage scores of students who watched the CAL package were superior.
4. The p-value for the retention performance percentage scores was 0.02.
5. The 95% confidence interval for the retention performance percentage scores was 0.83–12.19.
6. The effect size for the retention performance percentage scores was 0.8.
7. The level of enjoyment of students who watched the CAL package was higher.
8. The p-value for the level of enjoyment was 0.04.
9. The 95% confidence interval for the level of enjoyment was 0.03–2.75.
10. The effect size for the level of enjoyment was 0.7.

messages.content:
Statement: Students who watched the CAL package had superior retention performance percentage scores (p = 0.02, 95% CI = 0.83–12.19, effect size = 0.8) and level of enjoyment (p = 0.04, 95% CI = 0.03–2.75, effect size = 0.7) compared with students who read the information leaflet.
